column1: Table 5: Components of migration by administrative area, mid-2017 to mid-2018

1) Migration totals of have been rounded to the nearest ten at administrative area level, and the nearest hundred at national level. This may result in the sum of council area data differing from the national totals.

2) 2018 Council areas and 2018 NHS Board areas. The 2018 areas differ from the previous 2011 Council areas and 2014 NHS Board areas due to a small boundary change at Keltybridge (which did not affect the population), between Fife and Tayside.

3) The total in- and out-migration figures for Scotland equal the sum of migration from / to the rest of the UK and overseas. However, they do not equal the sum of moves for individual Council or NHS Board areas. Migration for individual Council and NHS Board areas includes people moving within Scotland. Since such moves do not involve anyone leaving or entering Scotland, they are not counted in the Scotland totals.
